# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js 14 project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Installed**: `@vercel/speed-insights@^2.0.0`
- **Package Manager**: npm (detected from existing package-lock.json)
- **Command Used**: `npm install @vercel/speed-insights`

### 2. Configuration
- **File Modified**: `website/app/layout.tsx`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout, placed after `<Analytics />` in the body

### 3. Files Modified
- `website/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component
- `website/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `website/package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies

## Implementation Details

### Framework-Specific Setup
Following the official Vercel documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I identified this as a Next.js 14.2.15 project using the App Router. The documentation specifies:

- For Next.js v13.5+: Import from `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Add `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout

This approach was implemented exactly as specified in the official docs.

### Code Location
The SpeedInsights component was added to the root layout file at `website/app/layout.tsx`, positioned alongside the existing Analytics component. This ensures Speed Insights will be active across all pages of the application.

